
@startuml

' Define classes
class Cinema {
    +name: String
    +theatres: List<Theatre>
    +copies: List<MovieCopy>
}

class Theatre {
    +id: int
    +name: String
    +seats: int
    +shows: List<Show>
}

class Movie {
    +title: String
    +duration: int
}

class MovieCopy {
    +id: int
    +movie: Movie
    +cinema: Cinema
}

class Show {
    +id: int
    +movieCopy: MovieCopy
    +startTime: DateTime
    +endTime: DateTime
    +published: boolean
    +status: String
    +seatsAvailable: int
}

class Reservation {
    +id: int
    +show: Show
    +customer: Customer
    +seatNumber: int
    +reservedAt: DateTime
    +cancelledAt: DateTime?
    +paymentStatus: String
}

class Offer {
    +id: int
    +reservation: Reservation
    +newShow: Show
    +validUntil: DateTime
    +accepted: boolean
}

class Customer {
    +id: int
    +name: String
    +email: String
    +creditCard: String
}

class Ticket {
    +id: int
    +show: Show
    +customer: Customer
    +seatNumber: int
    +issuedAt: DateTime
    +anonymous: boolean
}

' Relationships
Cinema "1" -- "0..*" Theatre: has
Cinema "1" -- "0..*" MovieCopy: owns
Movie "1" -- "0..*" MovieCopy: has
MovieCopy "1" -- "1" Show: provides
Show "1" -- "0..*" Reservation: has
Show "1" -- "0..*" Offer: offers
Customer "1" -- "0..*" Reservation: made by
Customer "1" -- "0..*" Ticket: buys
Show "1" -- "0..*" Ticket: has

@enduml

---

### 📌 Notes:

- **`+`** denotes public access.
- **`?`** indicates that a field is optional.
- **`*`** indicates a collection (list).
- **`DateTime`** is used to represent time-based values like show times, reservation dates, etc.
- **`String`** and **`int`** are primitive types used for simplicity.

